news.title: McKinsey & Co leases 45,000 sq ft office space in Mumbai's BKC
news.para: The total tenure of the lease will be five years, implying a total rental of nearly Rs 100 crore, said people aware of the matter.

news.title: AAR ruling making office refurbishing costs eligible for tax credit may lead to litigations
news.para: As of now, only the cost that contributes towards the output of a company — raw materials, input services, machinery, etc. — are eligible for input tax credit.

news.title: Gurugram: GPL Eden Heights' residents say developer violated norms
news.para: They have sought a structural inspection of the society by the department of town and country planning (DTCP), alleging that the conditions of the completion certificate have not been fully complied with by the developer.

news.title: Soon, a drive to recover Rs 400 crore dues from builders in Noida
news.para: Various government agencies, including the UP-Rera, the Noida Authority and the Greater Noida Authority, have already issued recovery certificates against these developers after having failed to recover dues from them.

news.title: Discharge plea of DHFL rejected in cheating case in Mumbai
news.para: ​The court said that while the representative appointed by the monitoring committee is discharged, the company would be prosecuted through the Wadhawan brothers who, it said, were responsible for conduct of its business.

news.title: US: Landlords look for an exit amid federal eviction moratorium
news.para: Most evictions for unpaid rent have been halted since the early days of the pandemic and there are now more than 15 million people living in households that owe as much as $20 billion in back rent, according to the Aspen Institute.

news.title: China Evergrande vows to resolve debt risks after regulators' warning
news.para: Financial markets are worried that any crisis at Evergrande could ripple through China's banking system as the company struggles to find the cash it needs to pay its many lenders and suppliers.

news.title: Net debt of listed developers declines 37% amid covid: Report
news.para: An ICICI Securities report noted that the decline in debt levels has been achieved through a combination of reduction in cost of debt by 80-160 basis points (bps), reduction in corporate overheads by 20-40 per cent from pre-Covid levels, operating cash surpluses, asset sales and equity capital raise either through the QIP route or through dilution at the SPV level.

news.title: Civic body to issue Rs 24 crore property tax notice to six Chandigarh department divisions
news.para: Though all these divisions are of the engineering department and the tax has to be paid by the department only, the UT wants the civic body to issue separate notices. This because the control or jurisdiction of the buildings falls under different divisions.

news.title: Karnataka government sets deadline of Sept 30 for UDAs to develop CDPs
news.para: The Urban Development Minister B A Basavaraja gave the directions to the commissioner of urban development authorities to submit the CDP within the stipulated time, a statement issued by his office said.

news.title: Equity raising critical for PNB Housing amid rising delinquencies: Ind-Ra
news.para: In line with the industry, PNBHF reported a rise in delinquencies for 1Q FY22 with GNPA of 6 per cent led mostly by the impact of second Covid wave which has disrupted borrowers' already weak cash flows.

news.title: Kolkata civic body lens on construction debris dumped in ponds
news.para: Formation of a special joint team comprising senior civic officials and cops has been planned to pay special attention to complaints from Metiabruz, Behala, Jadavpur and EM Bypass.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body notice to 200 houses in Sarangpur, Khuda Lahora
news.para: The civic body has given one month’s time to all the residents to divert their wastewater to sewage line or get ready for action that can even be disconnection of water supply.

news.title: Aurangabad civic body initiates steps to regularise Gunthewari properties
news.para: While the demand for regularizing Gunthewari properties is quite old, the latest amendment to Maharashtra Gunthewari Developments (Regulation, up-gradation and Control) Act, 2001 has rekindled hopes of owners of such properties.

news.title: South Delhi civic body makes sanction of building plans completely online
news.para: The department has completed work on a new module, which will accept applications online. To ensure uniformity, the new software will be used by all three municipal corporations, SDMC stated.
